title: Google\Cloud\Dataproc\V1\CreateBatchRequest
name: CreateBatchRequest
description:
A request to create a batch workload.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dataproc.v1.CreateBatchRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. The parent resource where this batch will be created.

params.name: data.batch_id
params.description: Optional. The ID to use for the batch, which will become the final component of the batch's resource name. This value must be 4-63 characters. Valid characters are /[a-z][0-9]-/.

params.name: data.request_id
params.description: Optional. A unique ID used to identify the request. If the service receives two CreateBatchRequests with the same request_id, the second request is ignored and the Operation that corresponds to the first Batch created and stored in the backend is returned. Recommendation: Set this value to a UUID. The value must contain only letters (a-z, A-Z), numbers (0-9), underscores (_), and hyphens (-). The maximum length is 40 characters.
